ter","organization":"Boston Latin School","start_year":null,"end_year":null},{"role":"Professor of Obstetrics","organization":"Harvard Medical School","start_year":null,"end_year":1885}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"science","header":"A classicist pressed into the family trade","body":"Reynolds excelled in the classics at Boston Latin and taught there two years before his father pressed him into Harvard Medical School. He took to obstetrics, and held the Harvard chair in the subject for more than two decades until 1885."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"He married a granddaughter of Paul Revere","body":"In 1859 Reynolds married Jane Minot Revere, granddaughter of the Revolutionary silversmith. The match folded the Revere line into a family already two generations deep in Boston medicine, with his father the founding surgeon of the eye-and-ear infirmary."},{"number":3,"category":"character","header":"His own grandson couldn’t name his colleagues","body":"A book of his medical correspondence passed to a grandson who, in 1913, wrote the hospital librarian that he could not vouch for the handwritten list of names inside or recognize the hand. The doctor’s working world had grown unreadable within two generations."}],"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"I01832","marriage_number":1,"date_year":1859,"children_ids":["HD6563","HD6564","HD6558","HD6565","HD6566","HD6567","HD6568","HD6569"]}],"cross_connections":[{"type":"family_orbit","related_id":"X03377","link_text":"Joseph Warren Revere","display_label":"his father-in-law, who ran the Revere copper works"}],"slug":"john-phillips-reynolds-1825"},"I01832":{"id":"I01832","classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"generation_from_thomas":null},"bio":{"display_name":"Jane Minot Revere Reynolds","first_name":"Jane Minot","maiden_name":"Revere","last_name":"Reynolds","married_names":["Reynolds"],"photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1781557106/147349069_c33ad113-e089-4369-8b36-126d5d693a53_zb5k1j.jpg","bio_blurb":"Granddaughter of Paul Revere; Boston matriarch"},"birth":{"year":1835,"month":6,"day":20,"city":"Boston","state":"Massachusetts","country":"United States","date_precision":"exact"},"death":{"year":1910,"month":5,"day":21,"city":"Boston","state":"Massachusetts","country":"United States","date_precision":"exact"},"parents":{"father_id":"X03377","mother_id":"X03381"},"tags":[],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM110"},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"HD6557","marriage_number":1,"date_year":1859,"children_ids":["HD6563","HD6564","HD6558","HD6565","HD6566","HD6567","HD6568","HD6569"]}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Through her, the Revere name entered Boston medicine","body":"Jane Minot Revere was a granddaughter of Paul Revere and daughter of the copper magnate Joseph Warren Revere. Her 1859 marriage to Dr. John Phillips Reynolds braided the Revere line into three generations of Boston physicians."},{"number":2,"category":"legacy","header":"Her son bought back the Revere house","body":"Among Jane’s eight children was John Phillips Reynolds Jr., who in 1902 purchased and preserved her grandfather’s house in Boston’s North End. The Revere ancestry she carried became the cause that defined his life."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Her name carried two Boston dynasties","body":"Jane Minot Revere bore the names of two old Boston families, the Minots and the Reveres, at the moment they joined the medical Reynoldses. Her children’s names, Paul Revere Reynolds and Mary Robbins Reynolds among them, kept the ancestry deliberately visible."}],"slug":"jane-minot-revere-1835"}},"burialCemetery":{"id":"CEM917","name":"Milton Cemetery","city":"Milton","county":"Norfolk County","state":"Massachusetts","country":"United States"},"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}